latestIgtvVideos.title: How I Pre-Poo
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
What's pre-poo? (I had a giggle when I heard this term for the first time! 😂) It's a treatment done before you wash your hair - pre shampoo.  I do this before almost every wash - either the night before or the day of using a heat cap.⁣⁣
⁣
First, I use @theinnatelife Scalp Treatment with a scalp massage.  I sped up this video to get to the point, but I like to take my time with this step.  It's so relaxing!  As you can see in the video, this scalp treatment is a thick liquid - a combination of oils and herbs. A little goes a long way!  I use the one for normal scalp, but they also have one for problematic scalp.⁣
⁣
Second, I dirty deep condition - applying a few pumps of The Innate Life Herbal Hair Mask on dry hair with prayer hands.  This mask is lightweight, so I don't risk over-conditioning when I use it overnight.⁣
⁣⁣
Why pre-poo?  The oil prevents my scalp from getting too dry during the washing process and softens the hair.  The scalp massage is relaxing and helps to start the process of loosening any buildup.  The hair mask provides extra TLC to the ends of my hair where I have the most damage and softens the hair to start the detangling process.⁣
⁣
You can pre-poo with any oil or treatment, but if you're interested in trying The Innate Life, go enter my giveaway posted earlier in the week - you could win a giftcard for these products!

When I started the transition to my naturally wavy curly hair after years of chemical straightening and damage, I had no idea it would be about so much more than hair.  It kick-started a self love journey I never thought possible.  It changed the way I think about beauty and how I see others.  It connected me with a community full of positivity and support.  It gave me the opportunity to express myself in new ways, and it changed my life for the better. ❤️

I'm always so so thankful to those who inspired me to start this journey, those who helped me to keep going when I wanted to give up, and those who come back again and again to support.  And I continue to create and engage in this community to pay it forward and help others.  Thanks for your continued support and for spreading positivity in this world.

latestPosts.caption:
This is Day 2 from Brush Styled Naked Curls

You can see the comparison from day 1 on the last slide.  I’m actually still very impressed with these brush styled naked curls!! 

To be expected with not using styling products with hold - day 2 naked curls have stretched a bit and are also fluffier/frizzier and less defined than wash day.  I’m loving it tho!! The soft, lived-in curls feel soooo summery!! I did a bit of a “witch”refresh using the @witchiloveyourhair Magic Mist (you can see a video of this on slide 2).

I have been experimenting a lot lately with “wash now style later,” #drystyling from @manesbymell and naked curls so if you’re interested check out my previous posts. I’m loving this soft curl era! And I’m loving the experiments! 👩‍🔬if there’s an experiment you want to see me try, let me know!

and THIS is why I love experimenting!  I definitely didn’t realize brush styling made this big of a difference for me. The only difference between these two wash days is that I brush styled on the right.  I didn’t use any products with hold (gel, mousse, curl cream). I brush styled and air dried.

latestPosts.caption:
It’s a Soft Curl Summer! 🌻When is the last time you did naked curls?! 

What is naked curls? It’s wearing your natural curls without using styling products.  Now I guess you could say a brush is a “styling product” but I really think of naked curls as being your curls without styling products that have hold - like gel, mousse, curl cream.  The brush really just makes sure my hair is detangled.  But since it does help to clump the curls, maybe we say it has undies on LOL!

The other day someone asked me for a tutorial of naked curls.  Normally I just scrunch and air-dry, but this time I wanted to see how brush styling would go without any hold products.  It was an excellent way to really see the impact a styling brush makes!! 

I did leave some conditioner in after squish to condish (I always do this!) and then I used a bit of the @k18hair oil on my dry hair to keep my hair from getting dried out.

I didn’t diffuse!  I air dried which I like to do in warmer months.  Naked curls dry so much faster too 🙌

Now let’s see how it holds up overnight 🤔

I forgot how much I love naked curls!! Remember #streakingwithlulu ?!🤣

Products used:

When the temps rise, I’m all about easy, breezy refresh styles that keep my curls out of my face. ☀️ 

For this look, I reached for my @curlsmith_official refresh faves:

✨ Miracle Shield for that much-needed heat + UV protection

You can find them at @ultabeauty or Curlsmith.com!

How are you styling your curls for summer? 💛

Day after #drystyling for the first time…

I did refresh a little but it was still looking pretty good for a day 2 (day 3? How do we count the “wash now, style later?” 🤣)

I’m still going to experiment more with this, especially over the summer when I like to air dry.  Chdeck out my last two posts about #drystyling if you missed them!

#drystyling - If you’re confused about this (I was too) keep reading. Yes this is different from a dry mousse refresh.

When I tell you I was skeptical!!! But seeing @manesbymell results, I had to try it. 

When I first saw this, I was confused because I thought it was a dry mousse refresh which I had done many times before. But it’s not that, because a dry mousse refresh is applying mousse to hair that has already been styled with styling products (likely the same mousse) the day before! Also, when I do a dry mousse refresh, I don’t spray with water.

When I realized it wasn’t that, I was confused because I didn’t understand why you would wash and condition your hair, dry it, then apply mousse, rewet it and dry it again?!! That just seemed like way more work on wash day than I had in me. 

But how this DID make sense to me was as a “wash now, style later” (@curlyfitmom ) situation where I washed, conditioned and detangled, then air dried before bed.  The next morning I applied mousse, sprayed with water, brush styled and diffused.

Breaking up my wash day like this was nice because my product free hair air dries much faster and it felt like much less work on wash day! (Plus it made me remember how much I like naked curls!!) Then the dry mousse styling the next morning actually took less time to dry than normal wash day, so in that way it saved me time.  Plus the results were impressive!

Just posted the video of how I did this so go check that out, and of course go see Mell’s video if you haven’t already!

I’ll continue to experiment with this - especially how much water and product to use. 

Oh and I used the @rizoscurls Curl Defining Mousse 🙌

latestPosts.caption:
Trying out @manesbymell Mell’s #drystyling eventho I was convinced this would be a fail…

When I tell you I was blown away!  I have applied mousse to dry hair before, but that’s for a dry mousse refresh when I’ve already styled it on wash day! Applying mousse to dry, I styled hair… 🤯
And this is why I love experimenting!

This brought back a few things I used to do more of that I want to revisit:

1) Naked Curls!  Omg I used to love doing naked curls (no styling products) and some of you might remember when we would go #streakingwithlulu 🤣

2) “Wash Now, Style Later” - such a great option for breaking up your wash day if you’re strapped for time! It was nice to wash and condition and air dry the night before because my hair dries so much faster without styling products.

I’ll be trying this again and experimenting with how much mousse and how much water I use!

Naked curls | curly hair | wavy hair | curly hairstyles | curly hair routine

I’d only ever used the @k18hair Molecular Repair leave-in when my hair was straight and detangled.  And I’ve loved it! I totally understand the hype 🙌

But I wasn’t sure how to use it in my curly routine because shampooing my curls and then towel drying them sounded like a recipe for a million tangles.

I used the @tootilab shampoo which is probably why my hair wasn’t crazy tangled!  Then I followed the K18 directions and was surprised how easy it was for me to brush it through.

After leaving it on for 4 minutes, I rewet my hair and styled with the @tootilab leave-in and gel. (PS use CURLICUE for 💸)

If you haven’t tried styling with a mousse, let this be your sign!

If you do love mousse, which one is your favorite?!

I love mousse because it gives volume and definition without the crunch that you get from gel! 🙌

Using the @curlsmith_official Volume Mousse and Oil

Y’all know I love the @bouncecurl brushes!  I have lots of videos showing both the OG define brush and the newer volume brush.  I also have a side by side video to show the difference. (Maybe I need to compile all of these into a carousel post 🤔)
